**The thesis:** Pete Hegseth as Enneagram Type 3 (Social 3, likely 3w2), built around the question "why does a man with the real resume still need the cameras this badly?" The hook is the 2015 Fox & Friends axe throw that wounded an actual West Point soldier; the skeleton key is his own line, "I joined the army to fight extremists in 2001. 20 years later, that same army labeled me one"; the tiebreaker evidence is the 32-day reversal on women in combat once the audience changed from a podcast to the Senate. The ending runs through his own book title (*In the Arena*) back at Roosevelt. Body is 3,612 words.

